 or weakly evolving\nstar-formation efficiency. This 'constant efficiency' model shows a similar\nevolution to our statistically derived $\\rho_{\\rm H_2}$, indicating that the\ndominant factor driving the peak star formation history at $z\\approx2$ is a\nlarger supply of molecular gas in galaxies rather than a significant evolution\nof the star-formation rate efficiency within individual galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 15 Mar 2021 18:00:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-05-12"}
