rves from independent wind sectors. The\nstochastic photometric variability of OB stars bears certain signatures of the\nline-driven wind instability. The distribution function of observed photometric\ndata shows negative skewness and the power spectra of a fraction of light\ncurves exhibit a knee. This can be explained as a result of the line-driven\nwind instability triggered by stochastic base perturbations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 15 Mar 2021 23:01:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-04-21"}
