 studies of the resonance strength and\nthe current transfer measurement. The impact of these uncertainties on the\n$^{23}$Na$(p, \\gamma)$ reaction rate is investigated, and it is shown that this\nrate requires more intensive study to provide the precision needed to constrain\nnucleosynthesis in globular clusters.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 16 Mar 2021 03:09:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-17"}
