hich bijective group state\ntransfer occurs at that time. We illustrate non-trivial group state transfer in\nbipartite graphs with integer eigenvalues, in joins of graphs, and in symmetric\ndouble stars. The Cartesian product allows us to build new examples from old\nones.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 16 Mar 2021 03:56:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-17"}
